What are the key things you would consider when creating/consuming an API to ensure that it is secure and reliable?
1)Error Handling :- 
		Design API to provide helpful error messages in case of exception.
2)Usage Limit :- 
	Set limits on how often a user or system can make requests to your API.
3)Valid Input :- 
	Check information you get from API so that it won't cause issues in your application.
4)Rate Limit :- 
	Respect the maximum number of requests allowed with API otherwise you will be blocked.